#descr "Although the world abounds with exotic marvels and mysteries, most explorers would agree that the mythical lands of U may be the strangest of them all, if not the most hospitable. Indeed, while barren, poor and uncivilized, they still retain a secret equally fascinating and unsettling, for they are populated by beings so bizarre that even when meeting them directly some have continued refusing to acknowledge their existence. These creatures of legend and madness, the blemmyes, are characterized by an extraordinarily grotesque anatomy, a primitive intelligence and a crude consonantless language. Seemingly straight up sprung from the silliest dreams - or maybe nightmares - of an absurd God, they look like disproportionate and hairless chimeras made of nothing but mistakenly assembled human bodyparts, most noticeably always missing a head, with their face - if any - being instead located in the middle of their torso. Apparently spawned directly from the earth by spontaneous generation, these sexless troglodytes actually believe that they originate from the remains of a dismembered deity like germs from a dead body, and that this properly Titanic entity, called Mu, is so ancient that it was killed by the first Pantokrator, and so gigantic that its belly would have become the whole world. Until now, blemmyes seemed to behave like mere cavemen, chaotic, wild, degenerate and ultimately harmless as long as their sterile territory was carefully avoided; but recently, this started to change. As the tribes of U gradually united under a mysterious call, increasingly weird and horrifying creatures have been sighted in its mountains, and it has been discovered that a new or resurfacing belief has emerged in the region, the concerning belief according to which the blemmyes' great Primogenitor shall soon be reborn in the form of a grand utopia, the imaginary Empire of Mu, which will finally let its children achieve their true nature and attain the glory they deserve."
